{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T00:51:06.912Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1780102266912_1","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-003@20260530T002730Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** Friday, May 29, 2026\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/limits.py`\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/__init__.py`\n- `tests/test_asset_bus_limits.py`\n- `sdp/implementation-plan.md`\n- `progress.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly enforces per-request ceilings as specified:\n- `MAX_IMAGES_PER_REQUEST`: 8\n- `MAX_MUSIC_DURATION_SECONDS`: 600\n- `MAX_TOTAL_OUTPUT_BYTES`: 256 MiB (268,435,456 bytes)\n\nThe `check_request_within_ceilings` function accurately estimates output bytes based on conservative upper bounds (raw RGBA for images, 16-bit stereo PCM for audio).\nThe `error_manifest_for_ceiling` function produces the required v0.1 `error` manifest naming the exceeded ceiling.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation covers image count, music duration, and total output bytes.\n- It handles missing `spec` or non-numeric fields by falling back to safe defaults.\n- It covers `asset_type` values of `image`, `music`, and `sfx`.\n- Other asset types (e.g., `voiceover`) are currently bypassed as they don't have defined ceilings yet, which is consistent with the focused scope.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows the established patterns in the `promptclaw/asset_bus` package. The use of a dedicated `limits.py` module for resource ceilings is a clean abstraction. Exports in `__init__.py` make these tools easily accessible to producers.\n\n## Security\nThe implementation provides essential protection against resource exhaustion (DoS) by untrusted requesters. By enforcing ceilings BEFORE starting the work, it prevents pinning the CPU or filling the disk. The use of conservative byte estimation is a robust security measure.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-documented with docstrings explaining the intent and behavior. The unit tests are comprehensive, covering boundary conditions and error manifest structure.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and meets all acceptance criteria. The addition of `render_args.py` (shell injection prevention) in the same commit was also reviewed and found to be high quality, though it belongs to a different task (T-002).\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-003@20260530t002730z-verify.md"}}
